\item Let $\vec{D}, \vec{E}, \vec{F}$ be the points that divide the line segment into four equal parts.

\item If a point $\vec{X}$ divides a line segment(here AB) in the ratio of m:n then its coordinates are given by
\begin{align}
\vec{X} &= \frac{n\vec{B}+m\vec{A}}{m+n}
\end{align}

\item From figure, points $\vec{D}, \vec{E}, \vec{F}$ divides AB in the ratio of 1:3, 2:2, 3:1 repectively. Thus there coordinates are given by
\begin{align}
\vec{D} &= \frac{1\vec{B}+3\vec{A}}{4} &= \myvec{-1\\7/2}\\
\vec{E} &= \frac{2\vec{B}+2\vec{A}}{4} &= \myvec{0\\5}\\
\vec{F} &= \frac{3\vec{B}+1\vec{A}}{4} &= \myvec{1\\13/2}
\end{align}

